<br>

<h2 align=center> KENYA</h2>
<p align=center>
<img src="../pix/kenya.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=2 width=428 height=271 alt="Map of Kenya">
</p>
<hr>
<br>
<b>Key National Statistics</b>

<p>Population	28.7 million

<p>Population growth rate	3.1%

<p>Under-five child mortality	90
(deaths per 1,000 live births)

<p>Rural population with	43%
access to safe water

<p>Adult literacy rate	75%
<br clear=left>
<p><hr>
<h3>Programme Overview </h3>

<p>ACTIONAID has been working in Kenya since 1974. Projects in six development areas are now reaching
more than 330,000 people. The principal goal of all these projects is to eradicate poverty by working
directly and in partnership with some of Kenya's poorest and most deprived people.

<p>The focus of much of ACTIONAID's work in Kenya is on helping poor communities to organise
themselves so they can develop and manage initiatives to improve their own lives. Specific support is
provided in savings and credit schemes, developing income generating skills,  improving access to
drinking
water, formal and non-formal  education and preventative health care. 

<p><b>In Kenya, ACTIONAID has:</b>

<p><ul><li> helped more than 53,000 people in the development area of Kyuso gain access to clean,
safe
water.

<p><li>established savings and credit groups in rural Ikanga so that farmers can take loans to buy
ploughs
and oxen, needed to increase agricultural productivity.

<p><li>worked with displaced and local communities in Kapsokwony, following tribal clashes in the
region,
facilitating reconciliation between groups and helping families rebuild their homes.

<p><li>created a network of community-based health workers in the slum district of Kariobangi,
Nairobi,
providing services such as immunisation, growth monitoring, family planning and treatments for
diarrhoea.

<p><li>supported local organisations such as the Nairobi based Know AIDS Society who provide
counselling
and public information on HIV/AIDS.
</ul></font>


