   <TITLE>Tibetan rug sale at selected Oxfam shops</TITLE>
   <META NAME="description" CONTENT="Oxfam shops are having are having a promtional sale of Fairly Traded, top grade wool carpets made by Tibetan refugees">
   <META NAME="keywords" CONTENT="Tibet, Buddhism, carpets, Chinese invasion, refugees, sale, Fair Trade, India">
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win16; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER><TABLE CELLPADDING=2>
<TR><TD VALIGN=baseline ALIGN=center BGCOLOR="#147CB5"><B><FONT  COLOR=#FFFFFF><FONT  SIZE=+1>PUT THE CARPET UNDER YOUR FEET-</FONT>
</FONT></B></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=baseline ALIGN=center BGCOLOR="#147CB5"><B><FONT  COLOR=#FFFFFF>
<FONT  SIZE=+1>AT OXFAM !</FONT></FONT></B></TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>



<CENTER><TABLE CELLPADDING=10>
<TR><TD BGCOLOR="#147CB5"><CENTER><IMG SRC="tibcarp.gif" HEIGHT=204 WIDTH=195></CENTER>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

<P><font color="#147CB5"<FONT SIZE=+1>Oxfam shops are running a special
promotion of carpets handmade by refugees from Tibet. Quality carpets are
on sale at selected shops across the region between the 10th and 24th of
February.
<P>Highly prized for their strength and lustre,
top grade wool is used to create each one of these exceptionally thick
pile carpets. Each carpet is made by up to 4 people often working together
at an upright loom. Woollen threads are knotted individually on a cotton
warp to create a pattern of beauty and detail. The patterns are uniquely
drawn from the ancient symbolism of Buddhist and Persian cultures. Motifs
signify blessings such as prosperity, good fortune, power and longevity.

<P>Following the Chinese invasion of Tibet in
1959, more than 100,000 people left Tibet and crossed into India. There
are currently estimated to be more than 130,000 people who are refugees
or in exile from Tibet. In 1981 Tibetan Refugee Self Help Handicrafts (TRSHH)
was set up with Oxfams help. Based in Delhi, TRSHH markets Tibetan carpets
and crafts world- wide thereby enabling many refugee producers to improve
their standard of living. TRSHH ensures that the conditions in which the
carpets are made are good and that a fair wage is received by the people
who make them. 

<P>Tibetan rugs look and feel beautiful anywhere,
even hung on a wall. As Spring approaches, Oxfam is pleased to offer a
rare opportunity to the internet community to purchase a beautiful carpet
made fairly and at an affordable price. 

<P><FONT SIZE=+1>PRODUCT INFORMATION:<BR>
</FONT> Each rug is 85 per cent wool, 15 per cent cotton<BR>
 Available in 2 sizes:<BR> 4 feet by 6 feet, costs £200.00 <BR>and 3 feet by 5 feet, costs £150.00 <BR>
 Dry clean only
<P>Fair Trade Tibetan Rugs are available in the following Oxfam shops:<P>
