<html>
<head>
<title>TVE - TVE NEW PROGRAMMES (Food for thought)</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#333366" vlink="#666699">
<font size=5 face=helvetica, arial>
<div align=right><a href="index.html" target="_parent">About TVE</a></div></font>
<h2>Food for Thought</h2>



<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial><b>ENDING HIDDEN HUNGER (20 )</b></font><br>

<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial>This report features UNICEF s work in eliminating deficiencies in three vital
micronutrients: iodine, iron and vitamin A. With examples from all over the
globe, the report clearly shows the major steps implemented on the programme.<p>
<b>Programmes and Language  Versions available</b>:<br>
<li>English version
<li>French version
<li>International version</font>
<p>

<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial><b>THE QUIET REVOLUTION (6 X 30 )</b></font><br>
<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial>A series of six dramatic, personal stories about individuals in Bangladesh,
Honduras, India, Nepal and Zimbabwe who are overcoming poverty, inequality and
environmental devastation to turn their communities into places of hope and promise.<p>
<b>Programmes and Language Versions available</b>:<br>
<li>English version
<li>International version</font>
<p>

<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial><b>PEST WARS (49 )</b></font><br>
<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial>A BBC-produced documentary looking at the favoured agricultural
practise of rejecting pesticides in favour of environmentally-friendly natural predators.</font><p>


<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial><b>MEENA: DIVIDING THE MANGO (13 )</b></font><br>
<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial>After losing most of her mango to brother Raju, Meena declares that
she does just as much work as he and should therefore receive the same amount of food at mealtime.
After swapping chores and meals for one day, Meena makes her point and, at the next family meal, they
are given the same amount of food.<p>
<b>Programmes and Language  Versions available</b>:<br>
<li>International version</font>
<p>

<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial><b>FIELDS OF TREES (30 )</b></font><br>
<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial>An antidote to all the depressing news about destruction of tropical
forests and looming food shortages. Communities in Africa, South East Asia and Latin America are
showing that, by working with trees, sustainable harvests can be made without expensive chemicals and
without felling all the trees in sight.<p>
<b>Programmes and Language  Versions available</b>:<br>
<li>English version
<li>French version
<li>Spanish version</font><p>



<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial><b>BRUNO BOZZETTO SPOTS (16 X 1 )</b></font><br>
<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial>A collection of sharp, funny morality tales from the Italian animator
Bruno Bozzetto designed to remind audiences that the earth s resources are far from infinite.<p>
<b>Programmes and Language  Versions available</b>:<br>
<li>International version</font>
<p>

<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial><b>FOOD FOR THOUGHT</b></font><br>
<font size=3 face=helvetica,arial><b>Programmes and Language  Versions available</b>:<br>
<li>	English version
<li>	International version<p>


<b>TAPE FORMAT & STANDARD REQUIRED</b><br>

<ul><li> inch High Band U-matic
<li> inch Low Band U-matic
<li>Betacam SP
<li> VHS (viewing copies only)<p>


<li> PAL
<li> NTSC
<li> SECAM</ul><p>



<b>PLEASE NOTE:</b><br>
following receipt of order, programme costs will be negotiated on a case by case basis and will
include dispatch and duplication charges; all broadcasters will be asked to complete a license
agreement prior to receiving the programmes on offer;viewing cassettes are available with exception
of Food for Thought which is currently in production; completed order forms should be addressed to
Catherine Hall at TVE and should arrive no later than the 1st October 1996, to ensure delivery
before the Summit (early November); if you would like to broadcast earlier on World Food Day (16
October), please let us know immediately; </font><p>

