lk.html">ODA press release</a> - Baroness Chalker, UK Minister for Overseas Development, confirmed she will be attending the conference.</ul><img align=left hspace=5 vspace=2 src="beijing_pix/dot.gif"><h3><a href="../oxfam/index.html">Oxfam</a></h3><ul type=square><li><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_beijing_press.html">The United Nations IV World Conference on Women</a><br>Press release<li><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_press_11aug.html">Oxfam's concerns for the UN IV World Conference on Women</a><br>At the pre-Beijing press conference on August 23rd Oxfam will focus particularly on what has been termed the 'increasingly female face of poverty'.<li><a href="../oxfam/beijing_brief.html">The Fourth World Conference on Women</a><br>Oxfams's briefing paper.</ul><img align=left hspace=5 vspace=2 src="beijing_pix/dot.gif"><h3><a href="../patp/index.html">People & the Planet</a></h3><ul type=square><li><a href="../patp/papt_press_july.html">The Fourth World Conference on Women</a><br>Press release<li><a href="../patp/pap_beijing.html">The challenge for Beijing</a><br>Cherry Farrow argues that environmental sustainability is as crucial to women's battle for social and economic justice as more commonly discussed issues, like health, education and development.<br><li><a href="../patp/pap_hands.html">Women holding hands</a><br>Women's groups are more effective and more visible than ever before. Collectivelytheir actions are changing the lives of people in households, communities and societiesthroughout the world.       <li><a href="../patp/pap_radio.html">A radio voice for women</a><br>Inspired by the Women's Peace Tent at the UN Women's Conference in Nairobi in 1985, Feminist International Radio Endeavour (FIRE) waslaunched in Costa Rica in 1991      <li><a href="../patp/pap_profile.html">These women call the shots</a><br>Modern methods of communication are helping to liberate and mobilize women, evenin the poorest communities - the story of a group ofilliterate film