k Bag - Ch 4, 8pm<img src="tvandradio_pix/whats_new.gif"></h3><ul>Return of the series that examines topical issues in Britain's black and Asian communities.<p><b>Love Doctors</b><br>Over the last few years, the UK has been flooded with African <i>marabouts </i> and West Indian <i>obeah. </i> These witch doctors and spirit doctors claim that they can cure impotency, put vitality back into love-making and bring home an errant spouse without delay. But are their insights and love-potions any more effective than a lonely hearts column, singles' club or dating agency? <i>The Black Bag </i> examines whether the love doctors are favoured only by the African and West Indian communities, or whether theiur "healing" appeal transcends ethnic boundaries. For many, they are the bearers of hope who repair damaged pysches - but can the love doctors really perform miracles for their clients?</ul><p><li><h3>African Footsteps - BBC2, 8pm</h3><ul>Well-known people make personal journeys through the continent of Africa.<p><b>Zimbabwe/ Malawi</b><br>Acotr <b>Timothy Spall</b> returns to Zimbabwe to find the real country he feels he missed out on when filming 'White Hunter Black Heart' with <b>Clint Eastwood.</b> Plus Malawian poet and hero <b>Jack Mapanje</b> is allowed home after a decade in exile.</ul><p><li><h3>Walk on the Wild Side - Ch 4, 12midnight</h3><ul>The fifth programme in a repeat of the hard-hitting, seven-part documentary series about young people.<p><b>Don't Be a Coolie</b><br><b>Kashir, Raza</b> and <b>Adie,</b> three young Birmingham Muslim boys, want two things in life - money and respect. This is the story of how they're going to get both through the simple philosphy of "scamming".</ul><p><br><a name="fri"></a><h3>FRIDAY 28th JULY<img src="../owo_logos/online_logotv&radio_line.gif"></h3><li><h3>Life After Live Aid - BBC2, 7.20pm<img src="tvandradio_pix/whats_wco.gif"></h3><ul><b>Bob Geldof</b> returns to Ethiopia to find out how the 'Live Aid' mo