<h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <a
href="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right>
<br>

<h2 align=center> ACTIONAID Ireland</h2>


ACTIONAID Ireland was established in 1983 as an independent Irish non-governmental development
organisation (NGDO). It supports long-term community development work through operational partners in
Ethiopia, Kenya and Uganda and is affiliated to ACTIONAID in the UK.
<p>

The money donated by individual supporters, the Irish government and the European Union funds vital
work in education, health, water, food security, community organisation and income generation. 
<p>

ACTIONAID Ireland also aims to increase awareness of the poor in the developing world through
development education in Ireland. Two resources have been produced to this end (with the assistance
of the National Committee for Development Education):
<p>

<ul><li>The Transition Year Option Guide to Kenya explores the cultures of Kenya and Ireland.

<li>Kids Like Us looks at the lives of Kenyan and Irish children through a cross-curricular book,
photopack and culture kit. 
	Suitable for 10-13 year-olds.
</ul>
Influencing key decision-makers at national and international fora to take account of the needs of
those in poverty forms another part of ACTIONAID Ireland's work. The organisation has consultative
status (category two) with the Economic and Social Council in the United Nations.

<p>

For more information, contact:<p>


<b>ACTIONAID Ireland, Unity Buildings, 16-17 O'Connell Street, Dublin 1, Republic of Ireland<br>

Tel: + (01) 87 87 911	<br>				Fax: + (01) 87 86 245</b>
<p>

<font size=2>ACTIONAID Ireland is a registered charity no. 6888</font>
</font>

