<br>
<h2 align=center> Help protect the future of those you care about</h2>


<p>
Have you ever asked yourself what would happen to the people you love should anything happen to you
unexpectedly? Would they be secure financially or might they come up against complications and
unnecessary costs in sorting out your estate? The answer may depend on whether you have an
up-to-date will.

<p>With the help of ACTIONAID's booklet, <i>Protecting their future is easy,</i> you can be sure that
by
making a will you have done everything possible to protect the future of your loved ones.

<p>So don't leave their future to chance. Send for this <b>free</b> booklet today.
<p>

<p>
Protecting their future is easy

<p>Written in plain English and split into three sections, ACTIONAID's booklet is a straightforward
reference
guide to the process of making and changing a will.

<p><hr>

<p><b>Making a will</b>
<ul><li>Why it is so important		<li>Getting to grips with inheritance tax
<li>Getting started			<li>How to reduce your tax bill
<li>Different ways of giving	<li>Aid that lasts - an enduring gift
<li>What to do before you see a solicitor
</ul>
<p><hr>

<p><b>Changing a will</b>
<ul><li>When to change your will and when to make a new one	
<li>Your legacy could help a community shape its own future
</ul>
<p><hr>

<p><b>Information file</b>
<ul><li>How to word a bequest and codicil
<li>Checklist for you and your solicitor
<li>Legal terms in plain English
<li>Current inheritance tax levels
</ul>
<p><hr>

<p><b>A gift to ACTIONAID in your will can change lives</b>

<p><i>"We made a will to ensure that our young children would be looked after. Even now they are
grown
up it is still good to know that for their sake things have been taken care of."</i><br>
Majorie Bunn, ACTIONAID sponsor, Buckinghamshire

<p><i>"It took courage for my family to send me to school. They lost the wages I could have earned.
But
they want me to learn. And nobody dares call me untouchable any more."</i><br>
Nagaraja, aged 11, Paragody village, India

<p>ACTIONAID constantly looks to the future. All our projects, which enable poor communities to take
control of their future, depend on long-term planning. Therefore funds must be available so that we
can
see projects through and ultimately help communities become self-reliant.

<p>Legacies left to ACTIONAID are used wherever the need is most critical and they have a major
influence
on our ability to undertake long-term development. With the help of a legacy, children in Uganda now
have
clean water, while in Chara Panchala, India, children are being vaccinated against fatal diseases.

<p>Wherever we use your gift, you can be sure that it will live on through the children of that
community.

<p><i>"A bequest to ACTIONAID will mean your concern for people in desperate poverty lives on in the
children you help."</i><br>
John Batten, Chief Executive, ACTIONAID

<p>
