<head>
<title>Supporting film-makers in the South</title></head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#333366" vlink="#666699">
<font size=5 face=helvetica, arial>
<div align=right><a href="index.html" target="_parent">About TVE</a></div>
</font>
<h2>Supporting film-makers in the South</h2>
<font size=2 face=helvetica,arial>While TVE co-produces programmes with broadcasters and independent
film-makers from
all over the world, it has a special remit towards film-makers in the South. Over the last 11 years TVE has
worked to promote programming that helps gives a more balanced view of the challenges facing the
developing world - and enables Southern producers and directors to make films that mirror their own
perspective on environmental and development issues. It was this approach which led to the pioneering
concept of Developing Stories which TVE developed with the BBC and the One World Group of
Broadcasters. 

<p>

On co-productions with Northern producers, TVE's policy is always to push for Southern crews and
technicians wherever possible. With grants from Novib in the Netherlands and the European Commission,
TVE has compiled Round the World Crews, a database of film-makers and technicians in developing
countries.</font>
<br clear=all>
<div align=right><small>Photo credit: Mark Edwards Still Pictures</small>
<pre>
</pre>
<a href="../index.html" target="_parent">TVE
Home
Page</div>
