<html><head><title>Rwanda: Special Report - News</title><!!keys: ></head><body><center><h2><font size=+3>R</font>WANDA: <font size=+3>S</font>PECIAL <font size=+3>R</font>EPORT </h2></center><img src="../owo_logos/online_logochrwandsp_line.gif"> <p><h1>Emergency News</h1><ul><img src="../unicef/unicef_pix/rw_dan.gif"><br><i>"There was scant attempt to single out the innocent from the guilty" - Dan Toole, Unicef's Rwanda representative, on the Kibeho camp massacre in April 1995 </a></i></a></ul><li><b><a href="../oda/press/mar26.html">Britain to give £8.5 million to Great Lakes region of Africa:</a></b><br>The ODA announces a new package of emergency assistance for Rwanda, Burundi and Tanzania, to aid sanitation, health, shelter and refugee needs.<p><li><b><a href="../gemini/mar96_rwanda.html">Rwandan street children learn lessons of survival:</a></b><br>Many orphaned or separated children are living rough on the streets of Kigali, refugees from 1994's genocide.  Now they are being taught new skills by relief workers.<p><li><b><a href="../oxfam/press13mar.html">For humanity's sake - heed the lessons of Rwanda:</a></b><br>Six of the world's largest private aid agencies have welcomed a report, which is fiercely critical of the UN's role in Rwanda before and during 1994's genocide.<p><li><b><a href="../amnesty/ai_kenya_rwanda_feb27.html">Former Rwandan minister survives assassination attempt:</a></b><br>Seth Sendashonga was formerly Minister of the Interior in the current Rwandan government.  The attempt on his life highlights the worsening human rights situation in the country.<p><li><b><a href="../amnesty/ai_rwanda_feb20.html">Amnesty - Urgent measures needed for Rwanda and Burundi refugees</a></b><br>The Zairean government is threatening to forcibly close the refugee camps on its borders.  This could lead to more killings, warns <b>Amnesty</b>. <p><li><b><a href="../amnesty/ai_rwanda_dec18.html">Criminal Tribunal indicts Rwandans suspected of ordering genocide</a><br>Amnesty International</b> is welcoming moves to bring the Rwandans who perpetrated 1994's massacres to justice.  But 60,000 people are still in prison, with little hope of a trial.<p><li><b><a href="../amnesty/ai_rwanda_dec12.html">UNAMIR's work in Rwanda vital, says Amnesty:</a></b><br>As Rwanda threatened not to allow the United Nations to stay, Amnesty International reminded the Security Council that much essential work, including the promotion of human rights, would be threatened if it pulled out.<p><li><b><a href="../gemini/wk43_gemini_rwanda.html">Radio replaces hate with hope in Rwanda and Burundi:</a></b><br>In Rwanda hate-broadcasts on the radio helped spark the genocide.  Now the BBC is using the medium to re-unite those who survived.<p><li><a href="../news/news_rwanda.html"><b>Latest update on the crisis in Rwanda and Zaire (Mid-September)</a><br></b><p><li><a href="../unicef/press_rel_mugunga.html"><b>Unicef evacuates unaccompanied children from Mugunga camp, Goma, Zaire</a><br></b>Unicef Press Release - 23 August 1995<p><p><li><a href="chrwandsp_soundrep.html"><b>Sound bites from Dan Toole, UNICEF Rwanda representative </a><br></b><p><li><b><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_update30.html">OXFAM Programme Update 30</a></b><br>Reports from Rwanda, Burundi, Tanzania and Zaire</ul><p><li><b><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_update30.html">Gikongoro camps - many killed in Kibeho massacre</b></a><br>OXFAM Programme Update - 28th April 1995<p><li><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_rwandese.html"><b>OXFAM urges Rwandese government and UN to protect civilians</b></a><br>OXFAM Press Release - 24th April 1995<p><li><a href="../unicef/unicef_rwandarep.html"><b>UNICEF Rwanda representative to visit UK</a><br></b>UNICEF Press Release - 27th April 1995<p><li><a href="../unicef/unicef_rwanda.html"><b>UNICEF reports appalling conditions in Kibeho, South West Rwanda</b></a><br>UNICEF News in Brief - April 1995<p><li><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_STCF_pressrelease.html"><b>Oxfam and Save the Children call for urgent action to prevent mass starvation in Rwandan refugee camps</b></a><br>Oxfam & Save the Children Fund joint press release<p><li><b><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_update23.html">OXFAM Programme Update 23</a><br>Reports from Rwanda, Burundi, Tanzania and Zaire</ul><li><b><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_update21.html">OXFAM Programme Update 21</a><br>Reports from Rwanda, Burundi, Tanzania and Zaire</ul><li><b><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_update20.html">OXFAM Programme Update 20</a><br>Reports from Rwanda, Burundi, Tanzania and Zaire<p><li><b><a href="../oxfam/oxfam_update19.html">OXFAM Programme Update 19</a><br>Reports from Rwanda, Burundi, Tanzania and Zaire</ul></ul><p><br><centre><img src="../owo_logos/online_logochrwandsp_line.gif"></centre> <p><h3><i>'One year after the genocide that left one million people dead - 300,000 of them children - Rwanda is trying to re-build.'  </i></b></h3><p><br><img align=left hspace=24 vspace=20 src="../owo_logos/new_more.gif"> <a href="chrwandsp_top.html"><li>Rwanda Special Report:  Contents</a></b><br><li><a href="chrwandsp_story.html">Feature stories</a><br><li><a href="chrwandsp_vid.html">Photographs and video clips</a><br><li><a href="chrwandsp_backg.html">Background</a><br><li><a href="chrwandsp_maps.html">Maps</a><li><a href="chrwandsp_help.html">How You Can Help</a><br clear=left><p><p><centre><img src="../owo_logos/online_logochrwandsp_line.gif"></centre> <p></body></html>
