<html><head><title>CHILDREN FIRST - EDUCATION</title><!!keys:UNICEF+children+Rwanda ></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff" link="#333366" vlink="#3399ff" text="#000000"><img src="unicef_pix/unicef_logo.gif"><br><hr><h3>EDUCATION - BUILDING A NEW FUTURE</h3><i>The entire educational system has been devastated by the Rwandan crisis.  During the emergency phase, UNICEF, together with UNESCO, initiated a Teacher Emergency Package (TEP) designed to start up from scratch the educational system in the country.</i><hr>A large number of children and teachers were the victims of the massacres.  School buildings were destroyed and looted.<p>The TEP or 'school-in-a-box' provides a quick response, self-contained mobile classroom, with one teacher can set up anywhere.  So far, 7000 TEPs have been distributed which cover the needs of 560,000 children.  More than 11,500 teachers have been trained into the TEP methodology.<p>Each school-in-a-box costs only US $170 and meets the needs of 80 students in two shifts, working out at a cost of just over two dollars per pupil.<p>The TEP is conceived as a bridge between the present situation and one where a regular curriculum can be imposed.  Together with the Ministries of Primary and Secondary Education and of Higher Education, UNICEF is working on the development of a school curriculum.<p>On 20 March 1995, 65,000 primary school students took an exam to graduate to secondary school.  UNICEF provided fuel and transport for the exam inspectors and $25,000 worth of school supplies.<p>In 1995, UNICEF and UNESCO are planning to rehabilitate 100 schools outside of Kigali.<p>According to UNICEF, 70% of the teachers in the primary cycle are either inexperienced or unqualified.  Therefore, a special emphasis will be given to teacher training.  School supplies and textbooks are also needed, especially to replenish TEPs.<p>UNICEF and UNESCO have begun the distribution of 400 TEPs to refugee camps in Eastern Zaire and Tanzania.  The training of teachers is also underway.<p>TEPs will be distributed in Kigali prison for detained children (in co-ordination with the Commission for Human Rights and ICRC).<p>An education for peace and reconciliation programme will be implemented throughout the year 1995.<hr>©Copyright  UNICEF. May 1995<hr><a href="index.html" target="_parent"><img src="unicef_pix/unicef_logo2.gif">UNICEF Home Page</a><hr></body></html> 
