<P><Br></p>

<H1>The Global School Project</h1>  

<P>School children around the globe share the same inquisitive desire to find

out more about the world outside their classroom. In the past this curiosity has

had to be satisfied by looking through atlases or encyclopedias. Now, the

Internet provides a new forum whereby children can learn from each other and

exchange ideas with their counterparts anywhere in the world. </p>

<P>The potential of this Global School is enormous; bringing children closer

together and creating a spirit of understanding and cooperation. The Global

School will also enable educational and training materials to be distributed to

any school linked to the Internet at almost no cost. Resources developed for

children in any country can be shared with schools throughout the world.

Interaid is involved in working with educational software developers in order to

build up a library of training materials fo distribution around the world.</p>

<P> To become part of the Global School, all that a school requires is a

computer, modem and suitable telecommunication link. Interaid is working towards

this goal by providing the relevant equipment and training to schools which are

not presently fortunate enough to have these facilities. Initially, this will

involve schools in the UK and South Africa but the long term objective is to

link up other secondary schools all over the world.

</p> 

<P><A href="#top">Top</a></p>

