<small><b><a href="guatemala.mov">RAMSAR and PACIPE - Friends of the Fishermen in
Guinea-Bissau</a></b><br>
Movie Clip: (2.4MB)</small></center>
<br clear=all>

<pre>

</pre>



<blockquote>
<h4>RAMSAR AND PACIPE - FRIENDS OF THE FISHERMEN IN GUINEA-BISSAU</h4>




One of West Africa's most significant fresh water lakes has become the focus
of local and international conservation efforts: the Lagoa de Cufada has 
become Guinea Bissau's first protected site under the Ramsar Wetlands 
Convention.<p>
 The development has triggered the formation of a group of local 
fisherman committed to using traditional netting techniques and "no fishing"
periods allow fish stocks to replenish themselves. PACIPE, a novel EC-funded 
public awareness programme, will ensure that the lessons learnt in protecting
the Lagoa de Cufada are publicised throughout the region.
</blockquote><p>



