<head>
<title>Comic Relief Why Not?</title>
<!!keys: Comic Relief+Charity Projects+information>
</head>
<body>

<hr>


<p><p><p>
<p><p><p><p><p><p>
<ul>


</ul>
<p>
<h2>Get involved yourself</h2>

Last Red Nose Day over 140,000 events took place across the UK, the press wrote over 3,500 articles in support of the campaign and more than 24 million people tuned into the TV show. We need to maintain this unprecedented backing to ensure the success of this year's event.
<p>
A small change in people's behaviour on March 17th will make a big difference to the lives of some of the poorest people in the UK and Africa. We want people think up crazy things to do, to get sponsored by their friends and family to do them, and then send Comic Relief the cash. After research into the most popular ways to raise a bucketload, We've compiled a list of the Red Nose Top Ten Best Fundraising Ideas Of All Time. They're all featured in <b>THE NEW FREE RED NOSE DAY FUNDRAISING PACK</b> - AVAILABLE BY CALLING 0891 665544.
<P> It also contains details of how to:<P>
<b>SPLAT THE BOSS</b> - people in offices, schools, on newspapers, in fact anywhere that has a boss-type person can raise cash through the glorious use of glutinous goo. We promise absolutely hysterical fun for absolutely everybody - exept if you're a boss - in which case this is disgusting. People can order their very own SPLAT KIT via the Red Nose Day Fundraising Pack.
<p>
This year is also the launch of the first ever <b>PET NOSE DAY.</b> It's time for family pets to no longer feel excluded. They can get their faithful owners out of the armchair for sponsored walkies or owner agility tests. We have scores of ways for pets to raise cash - they should start by ordering a free PET NOSE DAY PACK by calling 0891 333326<p>
Run your own <B>NOT A LOTTERY - THE COMIC RELIEF SWEEPSTAKE.</b> No million pound prizes this time, but the chance to help raise more cash for the Red Nose. Keenies are invited to organise their own sweepstake at their place of work, to have a flutter and win "not a lot ". Winners are asked to make a donation from their winnings to Comic Relief. Base your sweepstake on the grand draw of a Spitting Image sketch on the Night of Comic Relief.<p>
It is time for all energetic types to <b>BE A SPORT</b> and <b>GET YOUR KIT ON FOR COMIC RELIEF</b>. There is no sport playable in this country that wouldn't benefit from a special Comic Relief-ified Red Nose Day Match- Tiddliwinks between Teachers and Turnips, Rugby in Drag or a good old balls up.<p>
 

 


<a href="comic_launch.html"> click and see</a>

<p>
<hr>
