<html>
<head>
<title>Comic Relief How?</title>
<!!keys: Comic Relief+Red Nose Day 1995>
</head>
<body>
<hr>

<p><p><p>
<p><p><p><p><p><p>
<ul>


</ul>
<p>
<h2>NO BUSINESS LIKE NOSE BUSINESS</H2>
We state clearly at the point of sale for all Comic Relief products just exactly how much money is going to the charity. And then every penny of this goes to projects in the UK and Africa. All the production costs for the deals below are paid for by supporting companies, so there is no financial risk to the charity.
<h3>JUST SOME OF THE PRODUCTS</H3>
<H4>The Magical Human Nose</h4>
This year, the lynch-pin of Red Nose Day - that's The Red Nose - starts off a vibrant Red. But when it comes into contact with the heat of your skin, in a matter of seconds it turns magically FLUORESCENT PINK or YELLOWEST YELLOW. 
<H4>The Just as Magical Cold Nose for your Car</h4>
This is no ordinary Red Car Nose. Again it starts off bright red - but when the temperature drops below freezing it turns deep purple. Place your hand on it and create a hand-shaped red patch. <h4>The also Highly Magical T-Shirt</h4>
The key to this one is body heat.  Our exclusive T-Shirt carries an original design by Bang on the Door and responds to any rise in corporeal temperature - as your cool bits go hotter, its purple bits go pink and its red bits go yellow.
<H4>The Never Seen Before Clothes Nose</h4>
There is no excuse for anyone not to wear a red nose this year because of the new clothes nose, a classy pin badge. This new product attaches itself to any item of clothing and looks rather lovely.
<H4>Comic Relief's First Serious Song</h4>
The most ambitious music project to date is a special recording of LOVE CAN BUILD A BRIDGE sung by CHER, CHRISSIE HYDE and NENEH CHERRY, featuring ERIC CLAPTON on guitar. It's Comic Relief's first 'serious' single and is produced by Peter Asher. If it doesn't go to Number One, Lenny Henry will eat his next TV series.
<h4>The Comic Relief Screensaver</h4>
A truly original Screensaver, the perfect antidote to Executive Stress.  Say goodbye to that image of goofy goldfish popping up whenever your computer is idle - The Comic Relief Screensaver is excitingly interactive, endlessly changing, and actually witty.  It contains a year's worth of amusement for the office and a busload of prizes.
<p>
<p>
