<html>
<head>
<title>Comic Relief Whatever Else?</title>
<!!keys: Comic Relief+Charity Projects+Red Nose Day 1995+information>
</head>
<body>

<hr>


<p><p><p>
<p><p><p><p><p><p>
<ul>


</ul>
<p>
<h2>Ten things you may not know about Comic Relief</h2>
1.  Comic Relief will be 10 years old on Christmas Day, 1995. It was launched on Noel Edmonds' Late Late Breakfast Show live from a refugee camp in Sudan on  December 25, 1985. The single, "Livin' Doll" by Cliff Richard and The Young Ones was released in February 1986. 
<p>
2.  Red Nose Day 10 will be held in the year 2005. By which date Rik Mayall will be 47 and Cliff Richard will be 65 years old. (Currently Red Nose Days are held every two years.)<p>
3.  So far Comic Relief has raised over 92 million pounds. In the last 9 years they have sold 16,739,000 small red plastic noses - all recyclable. 
<p>
4.  The amount of money given by the public that they spend on Fundraising rhymes with Hero and Nero. They get all their fundraising costs sponsored through companies and gifts in kind. In fact, because of interest, more than 100% of the cash given to them goes to charitable projects.
<p>
5.  The last NIGHT OF COMIC RELIEF on BBC1 received more phone calls over the period of the broadcast than any other telethon to date.  
<p>
6.  The total money donated by the end of the television programme is usually doubled and on one occasion was trebled by the time the money stopped coming in.
<p>
7.  Over 72% of people questioned in  a MORI poll after the last Red Nose Day said they had taken part in at least one supporting activity.
<p>
8.  Charity Projects is the name of the charity that set up and organises Comic Relief. All the money raised is allocated to other UK registered charities to fund their projects.
<p>
9.  We love the general public, because without their continued support we just wouldn't be able to carry on the crucial work of helping some of the poorest people at home and in Africa.
<p>
10.  After 9 years in the business, we still don't have any idea how to spell Diaroea and Bikina Farso.
<p>

<a href="comic_launch.html"> click and see</a>

<p>
<hr>
